# PCAP conversations

This folder includes scripts to compare IBR traffic against normal traffic.

These scripts use the Monday-WorkingHours.pcap from:
http://cicresearch.ca/CICDataset/CIC-IDS-2017/Dataset/CIC-IDS-2017/PCAPs/

## Prerequisites

- Wireshark/tshark installed (for conversation stats)
- Python 3.x (if the plotting scripts are Python)
- The PCAP file: Monday-WorkingHours.pcap

## Generate conversation stats

From this directory:

Windows (cmd or PowerShell):
```
tshark -r Monday-WorkingHours.pcap -q -z conv,tcp > Monday-WorkingHours-stats-tcp.txt
tshark -r Monday-WorkingHours.pcap -q -z conv,udp > Monday-WorkingHours-stats-udp.txt
```

This creates:
- Monday-WorkingHours-stats-tcp.txt
- Monday-WorkingHours-stats-udp.txt

## Scripts

We use the following scripts to create and visualize conversations:

- plot-conversation-histogram-tshark.ipynb  (plots histogram(s) from the stats files)
- plot-conversation-histogram-wireshark.ipynb (alternative plotting using Wireshark export)
- conversor_tshark-wireshark.py (converts tshark output to wireshark format)

## Notes

- Make sure tshark is on your PATH (check with: tshark -v).
- Replace script names/args above if your filenames differ.
- Check the plot-conversation-histogram notebooks for more details on usage.
